Now I'll execute the network_fetcher tool to retrieve data from the API using the default URL parameter.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 30,
  "retry_count": 3,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I'll now execute the data_processing_parser tool to parse data from the default input file since the network_fetcher failed. This will provide structured data for the next validation step.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the data_processing_validator tool to validate the parsed data. Since I need a schema for validation, I'll use a simple default schema that allows any JSON object structure.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {}
    },
    "additionalProperties": true
  },
  "data": {},
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
